ary of being without gold in the midst of plenty. We wish to become men of means.', 11279, 0), (190573, 'There are so many torturous things in this life. Don''t let a man who doesn''t love you be one of them.', 1199, 0), (190574, 'If there were no women then men would still be living in the jungle.', 2586, 0), (190575, 'A woman always wants to change her man but a man wants her to be unchanged.', 2586, 0), (190576, 'Women often forget that the man she is complaining about is a creation of a mother like her.', 2586, 0), (190577, 'The true wealth of a man is not what''s in his pocket, but what''s in his heart.', 9273, 0), (190578, 'I never can imagine that a woman can do anything wrong, if they do then man made her to do it.', 2586, 0), (190579, 'Most often women want happiness and men want wilderness.', 2586, 0), (190580, 'For women, men creates war, even though women are the symbols of love, peace, and harmony.', 2586, 0), (190581, 'Women are lot more stronger then men, not just mentally but even physically, not only do they look beautiful in any form, but are also blessed with there caring nature which they have by birth.. What do men need more then this to respect a women??? Handling a family is equivalent to handling a big corporate office.. N she does it very well..Respect her beauty by praising it n don''t dis-respect it by passing dirty comments.. Some mentally ill men RAPE a women, but dis-respect every women including there mother n sisters with this act... and cause of such mentally ill men, every man is ashamed of being a Male/Man..', 17193, 0), (190582, 'The fundamental difference between the sexes is this: men make assumptions, but women rarely do.', 578, 0), (190583, 'Half the headaches in a man’s life involve a women and half the heartaches in a women life are because of a men.', 34766, 0), (190584, 'Men can be teenagers until well into their twenties. That is well known', 1621, 0), (190585, 'The trait I regard most highly in a man is kindness. Thoughtful, consistent kindness. All other qualities—whether charming, witty, handsome, enterprising, powerful, seductive, or ingenious—wither in comparison to a truly kind man.', 1456, 0), (190586, 'If the ultimate goal is lasting love, women are going to have to become comfortable with sacrifice and capitulation. Because those are the underpinnings of a long-term marriage – for both sexes.', 28493, 0), (190587, 'All men are what they are by reasons of the laws they keep and the thoughts they think.', 1660, 0), (190588, 'What was it with gay men and art photos of nude male torsos?', 34767, 0), (190589, 'Men will not save women for nothing, but themselves. Women have to save themselves.', 4238, 0), (190590, 'You may want the alpha, but the alpha has his pick.', 3711, 0), (190591, 'But what''s the use of arguing with a man? You belong, Mr. Smith, to a sex devoid of a sense of logic. To bring a man into line, there are just two methods: one must either coax or be disagreeable. I scorn to coax men for what I wish. Therefore, I must be disagreeable.', 1375, 0), (190592, 'Women have always moaned about men...but it turns out that their deepest complaints are reserved for one another, because while they expect men to be fickle, treacherous, and weak, they judge their own sex by higher standards, they expect more from their own sex--loyalty, understanding, trustworthiness, love....', 2065, 0), (190593, 'That''s the lovely thing about men, there''s no guesswork involved when it comes to arousal.', 31878, 0), (190594, 'We need more men to sit at the table... at the kitchen table.', 1770, 0), (190595, 'Men marry. Women wed.', 2892, 0), (190596, 'But it''s natural for men to compete against each other. We''ve been doing it since the cave days. Why else do we have wars? Wars are competition, no matter what the politicians call them.', 1720, 0), (190597, 'How frightening, that one person could mean so much, so many things.', 1753, 0), (190598, 'Men wouldn''t lie that much to the women 